WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:38.188 --> 00:40.247
[OWL HOOTING]

00:40.523 --> 00:44.857
Listen, it sounded like the brown-breasted
bottle-beaked hooting owl.

00:45.028 --> 00:48.725
Sherman, did you really bring me
all the way out here...

00:48.898 --> 00:50.866
...just to look at birds?

00:51.034 --> 00:52.331
SHERMAN:
I thought you liked birds.

00:52.502 --> 00:56.461
TREENA: Yes, but sometimes
there are other things I'd like to see.

00:56.639 --> 01:00.666
- Like what?
- Like a movie.

01:00.844 --> 01:02.175
[OWL HOOTING]

01:02.345 --> 01:06.304
Shh. Hear that? The owl is near.

01:06.649 --> 01:08.913
[CREATURE GROWLING]

01:10.553 --> 01:11.884
[RUSTLING]

01:18.128 --> 01:19.459
[GASPS]

01:25.535 --> 01:27.162
- Sherman.
- Yes?

01:27.337 --> 01:30.738
Does it have unusually large eyes?

01:30.907 --> 01:34.206
Oh, yes. I'd say so.
It's a nocturnal predator.

01:34.377 --> 01:36.607
And a giant pointy beak...

01:36.780 --> 01:38.372
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

01:38.548 --> 01:40.277
...and fur?

01:40.450 --> 01:41.781
[CREATURE GROWLS]

01:42.585 --> 01:45.281
You know, Treena, I'd be up for a movie.

01:45.455 --> 01:47.650
[TREENA SCREAMS]

04:05.295 --> 04:08.128
He did it.
Scooby-Doo captured the monster.

04:08.298 --> 04:10.027
Scooby-Dooby-Doo.

04:10.934 --> 04:12.094
[GROWLS]

04:17.106 --> 04:18.697
VELMA:
It's not a real monster.

04:18.875 --> 04:22.072
It's actually Miss Thelmer,
the company accountant.

04:22.245 --> 04:25.009
My plan was perfect. How did you ever...?

04:25.181 --> 04:26.773
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

04:27.750 --> 04:30.947
Hi, Mom. Can't talk, exposition time.

04:31.120 --> 04:32.849
What? Hang on.

04:33.022 --> 04:35.650
Will you take the wrap-up, Freddie?
I'm back.

04:35.825 --> 04:38.259
Miss Thelmer is actually a corporate spy.

04:38.428 --> 04:41.864
She pretended to be the so-called
Chemical Creep to scare people away...

04:42.031 --> 04:44.761
...while she stole
the company's secret formulas.

04:46.035 --> 04:51.098
From now on, the only books you'll be
keeping will be from the prison library.

04:54.243 --> 04:56.905
Well, another successful case is closed.

04:57.080 --> 05:01.039
All right, dude, I say we celebrate
with a party at the Burger Binge.

05:01.217 --> 05:02.445
Yeah.

05:02.618 --> 05:04.882
Burger Binge, Burger Binge.

05:05.054 --> 05:07.147
I've got a better idea.

05:07.323 --> 05:10.053
Shaggy,
you remember my little sister Madelyn?

05:10.226 --> 05:13.161
Little doe-eyes Dinkley?
Like, how could I forget?

05:13.329 --> 05:15.729
That's not nice. She really liked you.

05:15.898 --> 05:19.334
I'm sorry, Vel. Mads is a sweet kid.
We'll have to look her up sometime.

05:19.502 --> 05:22.665
VELMA: That time is now.
My mom wants us to check up on her.

05:22.839 --> 05:25.137
- Is something wrong?
VELMA: You might say that.

05:25.308 --> 05:27.970
Madelyn's going to a special school
for stage magicians.

05:28.144 --> 05:31.307
And, well, according to my mom...

05:31.481 --> 05:34.609
...the school's being threatened
by a griffin.

05:34.784 --> 05:38.743
Zoinks. Not a griffin.
I mean, anything but a griffin.

05:38.921 --> 05:40.149
Like, what's a griffin?

05:40.323 --> 05:42.450
A creature that's half eagle, half lion.

05:42.859 --> 05:44.349
Couldn't it make up its mind?

05:44.527 --> 05:47.155
It's a legend, Shaggy.
Mostly from medieval times.

05:47.330 --> 05:48.797
It doesn't really exist.

05:48.965 --> 05:50.626
I've heard that rap before.

05:50.800 --> 05:53.200
Come on,
we can't say no to Velma's mom.

05:53.369 --> 05:56.805
But can't we say yes
to a burger party first?

05:56.973 --> 06:01.376
SCOOBY:
Burger Binge, Burger Binge, Burger Binge.

06:09.452 --> 06:11.852
All right, Scooby-Doo, go fish.

06:12.021 --> 06:13.386
I can't, Shaggy.

06:13.556 --> 06:16.491
- Why not?
- I don't have a fishing pole.

06:16.659 --> 06:17.717
[GIGGLES]

06:18.161 --> 06:20.129
MAN [ON GPS]:
<i>Your next turn is 5 miles ahead.</i>

06:20.296 --> 06:22.025
<i>Watch out for the dips in the road...</i>

06:22.198 --> 06:25.361
<i>... not including the ones in the back seat.</i>
<i>Ha, ha. That's a joke.</i>

06:25.535 --> 06:27.002
<i>Pothole.</i>

06:27.170 --> 06:30.697
<i>Watch out.</i>
<i>Will you please keep your eyes on the road?</i>

06:31.140 --> 06:34.200
I'm not sure about the Mystery Machine's
new GPS, Fred.

06:34.377 --> 06:36.811
MAN: <i>Where did you get your license,</i>
<i>from a hobo?</i>

06:36.979 --> 06:38.742
I know, isn't it awesome?

06:38.915 --> 06:42.214
This is the magician school?
It looks like a castle.

06:42.385 --> 06:43.647
It is a castle.

06:43.820 --> 06:46.084
O'Flannery Manor originated in Ireland...

06:46.255 --> 06:48.689
...where it was known
for its mystical happenings.

06:48.858 --> 06:52.123
Back in the 19th century,
its owner, Lord Seamus O'Flannery...

06:52.295 --> 06:55.423
...had it transported to America
brick by brick.

06:55.598 --> 06:59.193
It says here that Seamus O'Flannery
practiced dark magic.

06:59.368 --> 07:00.392
[GULPS]

07:00.570 --> 07:02.504
Pretty creepy, eh, Scoob?

07:02.672 --> 07:04.606
Yeah, creepy.

07:04.774 --> 07:06.173
It gets creepier.

07:06.342 --> 07:07.400
When he passed on...

07:07.577 --> 07:11.411
...Seamus had himself entombed
in an island crypt on the nearby lake.

07:11.581 --> 07:14.846
Man,
am I happy we forgot our swimsuits.

07:15.017 --> 07:19.044
The castle was auctioned recently and cost
the magician a pretty penny to buy it.

07:19.222 --> 07:23.454
MAN: <i>Turn left at the next pine tree.</i>
<i>Left. Wake up, people.</i>

07:28.631 --> 07:30.223
Are you sure about this?

07:30.399 --> 07:34.199
MAN: <i>Relax, scarf boy,</i>
<i>we're taking the scenic route.</i>

07:34.370 --> 07:37.237
Everybody calls it a scarf. It's an ascot.

07:37.406 --> 07:39.465
MAN:
<i>Hang a right at the weeping willow.</i>

07:40.409 --> 07:41.842
<i>Right.</i>

07:43.045 --> 07:45.206
<i>Veer left at the rhododendron.</i>

07:48.317 --> 07:50.080
<i>Make a U-turn at the skunk.</i>

07:55.458 --> 07:58.586
MAN: <i>Ha, ha, ha.</i>
VELMA: Fred, this can't be right.

07:58.761 --> 08:00.956
FRED:
I better check the warranty on this thing.

08:02.565 --> 08:04.760
[ALL SCREAM]

08:06.169 --> 08:07.363
[MAN LAUGHING ON GPS]

08:17.013 --> 08:19.447
Hey, look, it's the road to the school.

08:19.882 --> 08:21.349
FRED:
There it is.

08:44.340 --> 08:46.274
- Jinkies.
GIRL: Velma.

08:48.110 --> 08:50.271
Madelyn.

08:51.347 --> 08:54.111
Oh, it's so good to see you.
You look so adorable.

08:54.283 --> 08:57.719
Oh, my gosh. I can't believe it.
You're really here. My big sister.

08:57.887 --> 09:00.355
- Hi, Madelyn.
- Hi, Daphne.

09:00.523 --> 09:02.423
Hi, Freddie.

09:03.159 --> 09:05.320
Hi, Scooby.

09:05.595 --> 09:06.926
[GIGGLES]

09:07.096 --> 09:09.121
[SHAGGY GRUNTING]

09:17.673 --> 09:19.334
Uh... Ha...

09:19.508 --> 09:21.066
Hi, Shaggy.

09:22.612 --> 09:24.739
Hi, Madelyn.

09:24.914 --> 09:26.006
MAN:
Welcome, everyone.

09:31.320 --> 09:35.256
I'm Whirlen Merlin,
maestro of the magical academy.

09:35.524 --> 09:37.151
<i>Alakazam</i>

09:42.298 --> 09:47.167
And this lovely lady
is my former stage assistant, Crystal.

09:47.670 --> 09:51.071
Hm. I guess this school
doesn't have much of a dress code.

09:51.240 --> 09:52.730
Yeah.

09:52.908 --> 09:56.207
Greetings.
I teach prestidigitary assistantship.

09:56.379 --> 09:59.940
I'm also in charge of caring
for our magical co-stars.

10:00.116 --> 10:02.107
[WHISTLING]

10:06.188 --> 10:09.089
This is Vernon, our star performer.

10:09.258 --> 10:12.227
But don't worry, he's a real pussycat.

10:12.828 --> 10:14.591
Nice to meet you.

10:14.764 --> 10:16.254
[ROARS]

10:16.632 --> 10:17.758
SCOOBY:
Yipe.

10:18.801 --> 10:20.428
One, two, three...

10:20.603 --> 10:22.298
...four. Phew.

10:22.471 --> 10:25.440
We better hurry. It's almost dark.

10:25.608 --> 10:28.975
Don't wanna be around
when you-know-what drops by.

10:29.145 --> 10:30.544
All right, Marlon.

10:30.713 --> 10:32.738
Marlon here is our resident stagehand.

10:32.915 --> 10:34.542
He runs things behind the scenes.

10:34.717 --> 10:36.480
We wouldn't have a show without him.

10:36.652 --> 10:39.212
Marlon,
please see to our guests' luggage.

10:39.388 --> 10:42.357
Already finished, boss. See you inside.

10:42.525 --> 10:46.120
Yeah, Scoob,
like, maybe we better go in.

10:47.163 --> 10:48.187
[GIGGLING]

10:48.364 --> 10:49.422
CRYSTAL:
Repeat after me.

10:50.833 --> 10:52.425
<i>Open, sesame</i>

10:54.003 --> 10:55.300
<i>Open, sesame</i>

10:55.471 --> 10:57.336
<i>Open, sesame</i>

11:06.415 --> 11:09.145
I hope you find your time
at O'Flannery Castle exciting.

11:09.652 --> 11:13.611
It's the grandest magic academy
in existence.

11:14.090 --> 11:17.025
Gee, I wonder where all the students are.

11:17.193 --> 11:18.455
I don't know.

11:18.627 --> 11:22.586
In their rooms, where it's safe.

11:22.765 --> 11:24.858
This is Miss Alma Rumblebuns.

11:25.034 --> 11:27.434
She was custodian of the castle
before I bought it.

11:27.603 --> 11:30.333
And now she's a housekeeper
to the students.

11:30.506 --> 11:33.407
This facility allows
performing animals only.

11:33.576 --> 11:34.600
[SCOOBY WHIMPERS]

11:34.777 --> 11:37.871
Oh, that's okay.
Scooby's been through training school.

11:38.047 --> 11:39.810
Yeah. Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

11:40.916 --> 11:42.907
[SCOOBY HUMMING]

11:48.991 --> 11:51.687
Whoa. Whoa!

11:59.268 --> 12:00.667
[GIGGLES]

12:01.404 --> 12:05.306
Oh, like, he was dropped on his head
when he was a puppy.

12:06.041 --> 12:10.375
Oh, very well.
I will show you your rooms.

12:21.157 --> 12:24.490
MAN:
Cone Castle commercial, take one.

12:25.227 --> 12:26.751
WOMEN [SINGING]:
<i>We're Cone Castle cones</i>

12:26.929 --> 12:28.794
<i>And we're healthy for you</i>

12:28.964 --> 12:32.058
<i>Run to your grocer and pick up a few</i>

12:32.234 --> 12:35.328
<i>Mixing grown-up flavors</i>
<i>Into kids' ice cream</i>

12:35.504 --> 12:36.528
WOMAN 1: Liver.
WOMAN 2: Onion.

12:36.705 --> 12:41.108
WOMAN 3: Broccoli.
ALL: <i>We're a gourmet lover's dream</i>

12:41.277 --> 12:44.212
MAN:
Hold it, hold it.

12:44.380 --> 12:46.644
Pardon me for halting the festivities...

12:46.816 --> 12:50.752
...but I distinctly remember paying
for a buttered Brussels sprout.

12:51.220 --> 12:55.020
WOMAN 4:
Ooh, um, sorry, I'm here.

12:56.192 --> 12:57.216
Oopsie daisy.

12:58.527 --> 13:00.688
Oh, for heaven's sakes.

13:03.499 --> 13:07.196
Can someone please manage this mess?

13:07.369 --> 13:08.393
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

13:08.571 --> 13:12.098
And you there, your cone is crumpled.

13:12.274 --> 13:13.605
Yes?

13:13.776 --> 13:16.904
AMOS:
Mr. Curdles, it's me, Amos.

13:17.079 --> 13:21.709
Remember when you told me
to call if any more students arrived?

13:21.884 --> 13:26.912
- I saw four kids and a dog.
- Four kids and a dog, eh? Heh, heh.

13:27.089 --> 13:31.048
Whirlen must be awfully desperate
if he's enrolling animals.

13:31.227 --> 13:34.924
Perhaps they'll get another visit
from the you-know-what.

13:35.097 --> 13:39.796
He's showing up almost nightly these days
and getting bolder each time.

13:39.969 --> 13:42.369
<i>I'd hate to think</i>
<i>what could happen tonight.</i>

13:42.538 --> 13:45.302
I'm sure you'll let me know.

13:47.176 --> 13:48.507
[SPLAT]

13:50.813 --> 13:55.147
Will no one dab up this dairy?

13:55.885 --> 13:58.877
MADELYN: They say Lord O'Flannery
practiced real magic.

13:59.054 --> 14:01.921
And that he had many secrets
built into the castle walls.

14:02.091 --> 14:05.254
Legend has it that he even conjured up
a griffin to protect it...

14:05.427 --> 14:07.520
...and housed the monster
in that old tower...

14:08.297 --> 14:11.095
...called the Griffin's Roost.

14:11.267 --> 14:13.360
Why doesn't Whirlen Merlin
knock it down...

14:13.536 --> 14:15.504
...and put up a student union
or something?

14:15.671 --> 14:19.607
He's hoping to restore it someday.
But until then, it's off-limits.

14:19.775 --> 14:22.608
His career goes all the way back
to when he was a kid.

14:22.778 --> 14:24.871
He started
with neighborhood puppet shows.

14:25.047 --> 14:27.447
Oh, and over here is his trophy case.

14:27.616 --> 14:29.846
This is Whirlen Merlin
when he was onstage.

14:30.019 --> 14:31.179
Isn't he awesome?

14:31.353 --> 14:34.117
I had no idea you were so into magic,
Madelyn.

14:34.290 --> 14:36.588
At least you've finally settled
on something.

14:36.759 --> 14:39.319
Where were you last semester,
clown college?

14:39.495 --> 14:43.363
Heh, heh. Yeah,
so I've done some soul searching.

14:43.532 --> 14:46.558
Not everyone is born
with a mystery book in her hand, Velma.

14:46.735 --> 14:48.498
Well, I think magic is really cool.

14:48.671 --> 14:51.071
I've always been fascinated
by how it's done.

14:51.240 --> 14:53.401
Just as Velma loves to solve mysteries...

14:53.576 --> 14:58.240
...I love to uncover the secrets of magic,
and this is the perfect school for that.

14:58.414 --> 15:00.678
What about that griffin? Mom said...

15:00.849 --> 15:03.511
Mom's just dramatic.
It's a silly old myth.

15:03.686 --> 15:05.677
[GONG CLANGING]

15:09.892 --> 15:11.291
That's our dinner bell.

15:11.460 --> 15:12.484
<i>Alakazam</i>

15:15.364 --> 15:18.060
And because
you're our special guests of honor...

15:18.233 --> 15:20.428
...I've asked the chef...

15:21.136 --> 15:22.194
That's me.

15:22.371 --> 15:24.532
- To prepare a royal feast.

15:24.707 --> 15:25.969
A feast.

15:26.141 --> 15:29.440
Like, I think he said the magic word.

15:37.419 --> 15:41.446
The guests of honor
almost outnumber the students.

15:41.624 --> 15:42.886
And where are the teachers?

15:43.058 --> 15:47.222
A lot of them left
thanks to that scary old griffin...

15:47.596 --> 15:49.791
...which no one has ever seen, of course.

15:50.866 --> 15:54.324
Before we start, a little dinner lighting.

15:54.503 --> 15:55.595
<i>Alakazam</i>

16:01.410 --> 16:03.241
[ALL GASP]

16:04.913 --> 16:08.940
Far out. Dinner by candlelight.

16:09.284 --> 16:11.411
How romantic.

16:12.221 --> 16:14.018
SCOOBY:
Let's eat.

16:16.625 --> 16:17.990
[GASPS]

16:18.994 --> 16:21.792
Gee, Scoob,
I think it's a little undercooked.

16:21.964 --> 16:23.295
[LAUGHING]

16:23.465 --> 16:29.097
<i>Do not worry, never fear</i>
<i>Your favorite dish will now appear</i>

16:31.073 --> 16:37.444
Pinch me, Scooby-Doo, extra cheesy
cheese pizza with a side of pickles.

16:41.950 --> 16:46.148
Scooby Snacks
in cherry sauce and whipped cream.

16:50.392 --> 16:52.622
Ho, ho, ho.

16:54.830 --> 16:57.298
Wow. Whirlen is amazing.

16:57.733 --> 17:00.099
- Aw.
- I cooked it.

17:01.103 --> 17:03.094
[THUNDER CRASHING]

17:09.278 --> 17:10.301
What's that?

17:40.342 --> 17:42.970
It's a devil of a night out there.

17:44.546 --> 17:51.315
The kind of night that invites ghosts
and goblins and other visitors.

17:51.587 --> 17:56.684
Uh, Miss Rumblebuns, is it okay
if some of us go back to our rooms?

17:56.859 --> 17:58.952
I suppose so.

18:04.767 --> 18:06.496
Psst. Shaggy, come on.

18:06.668 --> 18:09.865
While everyone else is eating,
I wanna show you something special.

18:10.038 --> 18:12.905
- Like, now?
- Yes, while the moon is still out.

18:13.075 --> 18:16.067
I promise you're going to find it
very, very exciting.

18:16.245 --> 18:22.275
You know, Madelyn,
I find this pizza very, very, very exciting.

18:22.518 --> 18:24.145
MADELYN:
Come on.

18:35.164 --> 18:38.133
Are you sure you wanna go out in the dark?
It's kind of spooky.

18:38.300 --> 18:40.734
Amos the groundskeeper
is always out after dark.

18:40.903 --> 18:43.701
Yeah, well,
that dude's totally spooky too.

18:43.872 --> 18:47.137
What I wanna show is something
that was brought here with the castle...

18:47.309 --> 18:49.937
...over two centuries ago.

18:50.212 --> 18:52.237
[OWL HOOTING]

18:54.783 --> 18:57.411
Hurry, guys, it's right around the bend.

19:10.165 --> 19:12.190
Here we are.

19:17.906 --> 19:21.398
I found a picture of this sundial
on one of the castle walls.

19:26.915 --> 19:31.716
When the moon is full
and you twist it like so...

19:53.775 --> 19:55.072
That's Seamus O'Flannery...

19:55.244 --> 19:57.974
...the man who brought the castle over here
from Ireland.

19:58.146 --> 20:01.809
Wow. Like, dig that crazy toothpick.

20:02.317 --> 20:07.880
Shaggy, that's the magic staff used
to summon and control the griffin.

20:08.056 --> 20:10.183
I thought you said
the griffin was a myth.

20:10.359 --> 20:12.384
I didn't want the others to be frightened.

20:12.561 --> 20:14.859
I'm telling you because you're brave.

20:15.030 --> 20:18.124
Brave? Shaggy? Brave?

20:18.300 --> 20:20.325
[LAUGHING]

20:21.670 --> 20:23.035
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:23.205 --> 20:25.173
Sorry.

20:27.709 --> 20:30.371
Like, what's all this gruesome graffiti?

20:30.545 --> 20:35.175
It says, "Winged protector,
arise and guard this castle."

20:35.350 --> 20:37.341
[GROWLING]

20:39.221 --> 20:42.486
Don't look now. But I think it's arisen.

21:08.884 --> 21:10.875
[SCREECHING]

21:12.054 --> 21:14.045
[PANTING AND GRUNTING]

21:27.269 --> 21:29.396
SHAGGY:
Through here.

21:30.472 --> 21:31.962
Down.

21:33.976 --> 21:35.273
Good thinking, Shaggy.

21:35.444 --> 21:36.843
Like, who's thinking?

21:37.012 --> 21:38.070
[GRIFFIN SCREECHES]

21:41.917 --> 21:46.081
Did you see how Whirlen Merlin
made that dessert appear out of nowhere?

21:46.254 --> 21:48.484
Not really. I was watching Crystal.

21:48.657 --> 21:50.124
All she did was point.

21:50.292 --> 21:53.284
It's the way she did it so effortlessly.

21:53.462 --> 21:54.861
I can point too.

21:55.030 --> 21:58.090
Usually when you do
you knock my glasses off.

21:58.266 --> 22:01.292
Easy, Velma.
She hasn't done that in at least an hour.

22:01.570 --> 22:03.561
Ha, ha. Very funny, scarf boy.

22:04.606 --> 22:05.937
[MADELYN SCREAMING]

22:06.108 --> 22:07.575
SHAGGY:
Griffin!

22:09.444 --> 22:11.935
It's the griffin!

22:20.455 --> 22:22.286
Oh, my gosh, there it is.

22:22.457 --> 22:25.358
That's right, Daddy.
I told you it was real.

22:27.696 --> 22:29.459
Holy Houdini.

22:30.265 --> 22:32.961
SHAGGY:
<i>Open sesame, open sesame</i>

22:33.135 --> 22:35.296
<i>Open sesame now</i>

22:40.475 --> 22:42.443
This way, guys.

22:48.850 --> 22:50.841
[SCREECHES]

22:54.523 --> 22:55.649
[SHUTTER CLICKS]

23:02.364 --> 23:07.301
When I enrolled Maxwell in your school
I didn't expect dodging monsters...

23:07.469 --> 23:10.734
...to be a part of the curriculum.
Good day, sir.

23:10.906 --> 23:14.637
But we didn't know the griffin
was real.

23:14.810 --> 23:19.110
Poor Whirlen.
There go the rest of his students.

23:20.949 --> 23:22.143
Where are you going?

23:22.317 --> 23:25.252
Aren't we taking Madelyn home
because of the griffin?

23:25.420 --> 23:28.583
No, Shaggy. The griffin has us curious.

23:36.231 --> 23:38.222
[CHUCKLES]

23:38.767 --> 23:40.359
Oh, looks like school's out.

23:40.535 --> 23:44.062
- Who's he?
- Calvin Curdles, the cone king.

23:44.239 --> 23:47.936
He's been trying to buy O'Flannery Castle
since Whirlen beat him in the auction.

23:48.510 --> 23:51.104
Alma, you look lovely as always.

23:51.279 --> 23:53.907
Oh, here, have a sardine in castor oil.

23:54.082 --> 23:57.347
It will enhance your lovely complexion.

23:57.519 --> 24:01.546
Don't try to con me
with your cones, Calvin.

24:03.892 --> 24:06.224
Thought I'd bring something
for the kiddies.

24:06.394 --> 24:10.626
Oh. But I see there aren't any kiddies left.

24:14.569 --> 24:16.434
[BOTH GASP]

24:16.605 --> 24:19.369
I told you, Curdles, I'm not ready to sell.

24:19.541 --> 24:20.565
Really?

24:20.742 --> 24:23.643
Not even
after your little pest-control problem?

24:23.812 --> 24:26.212
The magic academy has been my dream
for years.

24:26.381 --> 24:29.748
And we're not about to give it up
for one little scare. Are we, gang?

24:29.918 --> 24:33.285
- No way.
- Well... Uh...

24:33.455 --> 24:35.946
Why do you want the castle,
Mr. Curdles?

24:36.124 --> 24:39.287
Well, my inquisitive little miss...

24:39.461 --> 24:44.694
...my dream is to retool it
into my flagship restaurant.

24:44.866 --> 24:47.460
Then I'll open more restaurants.

24:47.636 --> 24:50.764
Soon I'll have kids all over the world...

24:50.939 --> 24:56.741
...eating my vegetable
and variety meat-flavored ice-cream cones.

24:56.912 --> 25:00.245
But won't the griffin scare away
all your customers?

25:01.349 --> 25:03.613
Yes. Well, uh...

25:03.785 --> 25:08.779
...I really don't believe
in things I don't believe in.

25:08.957 --> 25:10.618
Neither do we, Mr. Curdles.

25:10.792 --> 25:12.783
Which is why we intend to investigate.

25:12.961 --> 25:17.227
Griffin or no griffin,
my offer won't be around forever, Whirlen.

25:17.399 --> 25:18.957
I suggest you reconsider.

25:19.568 --> 25:21.536
Soon.

25:34.783 --> 25:36.273
Hmph.

25:39.721 --> 25:42.451
Call me if you hear anything.

25:46.094 --> 25:48.187
He's right. I don't know what to do.

25:48.363 --> 25:50.923
We've got a school and no one to teach.

25:51.099 --> 25:52.191
You still have me.

25:52.367 --> 25:55.530
I wouldn't mind
taking one of your classes.

25:55.704 --> 25:58.730
- That might not be a bad idea.
- What?

25:58.907 --> 26:01.432
We should take some classes
to learn more about magic.

26:01.610 --> 26:03.635
It could help us with our investigation.

26:03.812 --> 26:06.440
We would be delighted to teach you.

26:06.615 --> 26:11.882
The full faculty of the Whirlen Merlin
Academy of Magic is at your command.

28:33.628 --> 28:34.959
[SCREAMS]

28:35.764 --> 28:36.788
[SIGHS]

28:43.705 --> 28:45.036
Hm.

28:50.078 --> 28:51.477
What in the world?

28:51.646 --> 28:53.637
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

29:15.737 --> 29:17.261
DAPHNE:
Whoa.

29:17.939 --> 29:19.429
VELMA:
Daphne?

29:19.607 --> 29:20.631
Hey, Vel.

29:20.809 --> 29:21.833
What's going on?

29:22.343 --> 29:24.470
I'm tired of being klutzy old Daphne.

29:24.646 --> 29:29.948
From now on I'm dazzling Daphne.
Centered, controlled, graceful.

29:30.118 --> 29:33.554
Does this have anything to do
with Fred going gaga over Crystal?

29:33.721 --> 29:35.416
No.

29:41.429 --> 29:43.056
Maybe.

29:43.231 --> 29:44.960
Why are you snooping at this hour?

29:45.133 --> 29:48.125
I thought you'd be doing
the sisterly slumber party with Madelyn.

29:48.303 --> 29:49.895
VELMA:
It's great to see Mads again...

29:50.071 --> 29:52.596
...but we don't seem to have
that much in common.

29:52.774 --> 29:55.607
Just between you and me,
she's kind of a nerd.

29:55.777 --> 29:56.937
No kidding.

29:57.111 --> 30:00.080
Once she gloms onto something,
there's no stopping her.

30:00.248 --> 30:03.706
She's always over-analyzing
every little thing that attracts her attention.

30:04.018 --> 30:09.149
Hmm. There's some gritty residue
on the floor. Could be a clue.

30:09.524 --> 30:13.119
- It's rosin. Dancers put it on their shoes.
- I knew that.

30:13.595 --> 30:17.827
Yeah, you and your sister
are like night and day.

30:17.999 --> 30:19.990
[GRUNTING]

30:24.239 --> 30:25.934
It must be stuck.

30:26.107 --> 30:28.837
- A little help?
- Sure.

30:30.411 --> 30:34.472
DAPHNE: Thanks. Nothing like a workout
to control the klutziness.

30:35.250 --> 30:36.649
[BOTH GROAN]

30:41.089 --> 30:43.853
That wasn't klutziness.
That happened on its own.

30:44.025 --> 30:45.652
Come on.

30:53.601 --> 30:55.466
[BAT SCREECHES AND BOTH SCREAM]

31:05.914 --> 31:09.873
This stuff must have been shipped over
from Ireland along with the castle.

31:11.352 --> 31:13.081
Some of this is more recent.

31:13.254 --> 31:17.156
This photo album can't be more
than 20 years old. Jinkies.

31:17.325 --> 31:19.054
Isn't that Miss Rumblebuns?

31:19.227 --> 31:21.457
It's hard to tell. She's smiling.

31:21.629 --> 31:24.223
Madelyn says
Alma's worked here all her life.

31:24.399 --> 31:26.799
Even before Whirlen won it in an auction.

31:26.968 --> 31:29.596
This castle's like her home.

31:29.971 --> 31:32.303
BOTH:
Oh, my gosh.

31:32.874 --> 31:34.603
DAPHNE:
That's Mr. Curdles.

31:34.776 --> 31:38.678
VELMA: They must have been boyfriend
and girlfriend. It takes all kinds.

31:38.846 --> 31:40.711
DAPHNE:
I guess.

31:40.882 --> 31:42.543
- Ooh.
- Ew.

31:43.284 --> 31:47.050
We have to build up our energy
in case we see that creepy griffin again.

31:47.221 --> 31:49.553
Like, who can run away
on an empty stomach?

31:49.724 --> 31:50.884
Not me.

31:51.125 --> 31:53.116
[CREATURE GROWLING]

31:54.829 --> 31:57.593
I think we hit that kitchen
in the nick of time, Scoob.

31:57.765 --> 31:59.164
[CREATURE CONTINUES GROWLING]

31:59.601 --> 32:02.069
Like, your tummy is growling.

32:02.236 --> 32:03.362
Not my tummy.

32:05.974 --> 32:10.411
Well, if it's not your tummy,
and it's not my tummy...

32:12.246 --> 32:14.180
...like, it's his tummy.

32:14.682 --> 32:16.673
[BOTH SCREAM]

32:21.556 --> 32:22.921
Scoob.

32:28.229 --> 32:31.790
Zoinks. A dead end. Nowhere to hide.

32:31.966 --> 32:33.934
Look.

32:38.306 --> 32:40.297
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

32:46.114 --> 32:48.105
[BIRD CHIRPING]

32:51.986 --> 32:53.146
SCOOBY:
Phew.

32:55.823 --> 32:56.847
Hello.

32:57.025 --> 32:59.050
[ROARS]

33:08.136 --> 33:11.162
Like, come on, Scoob,
make friends with the nice kitty cat.

33:11.773 --> 33:12.933
[ROARS]

33:13.641 --> 33:15.438
BOTH:
Yikes!

33:15.910 --> 33:18.743
On second thought,
let's let him eat in peace.

33:22.250 --> 33:24.241
[SHAGGY PANTING]

33:31.025 --> 33:33.016
[WHIMPERING]

33:37.765 --> 33:39.926
Hey, look.

33:42.070 --> 33:43.970
Puppets.

33:44.605 --> 33:48.701
Like, this must be where they store
their Halloween decorations.

33:49.577 --> 33:53.343
Hey, Scoob, how many times have we run
into goons like this?

33:53.514 --> 33:57.610
"And I would've got away with it too
if it weren't for you meddling kids."

33:57.785 --> 33:59.685
[LAUGHING]

34:00.221 --> 34:02.086
"And your dog too."

34:02.256 --> 34:03.587
[CLEARS THROAT]

34:07.695 --> 34:10.357
What are you doing in here?

34:10.531 --> 34:13.329
Like, uh, we were just...

34:13.501 --> 34:15.900
No one is allowed in this room.

34:22.342 --> 34:26.677
Not students, not visitors,
and especially not fleabags.

34:28.815 --> 34:30.909
[TECHNO MUSIC PLAYING]

34:31.853 --> 34:33.445
- Huh?
- Huh?

34:43.563 --> 34:44.860
[BOTH YELP]

34:48.002 --> 34:51.233
Like, dude, how do you get out of here?

34:51.405 --> 34:55.603
Scooby? Scooby-Doo, where are you?

34:58.379 --> 35:00.279
Hey, who killed the light show?

35:00.448 --> 35:02.245
CRYSTAL:
Just me.

35:03.017 --> 35:05.212
That was scary.

35:06.521 --> 35:08.682
[GIGGLES THEN YELPS]

35:09.824 --> 35:11.917
- Shaggy.
MARLON: Oh, dear.

35:16.864 --> 35:18.388
What is this place?

35:18.566 --> 35:19.760
It's my private workroom.

35:19.934 --> 35:22.801
This is where I create props and illusions
for the students.

35:22.970 --> 35:26.030
I heard noises
and found these two snooping around.

35:26.207 --> 35:30.439
No harm done, Miss Alma.
I'm happy to give them a demonstration.

35:36.551 --> 35:37.643
That's amazing.

35:37.819 --> 35:41.152
Thank you.
It's a three-dimensional volumetric display.

35:41.322 --> 35:44.985
Think of it as an upgrade on, you know,
your traditional hologram.

35:45.159 --> 35:47.992
WHIRLEN: Yes, my big brother's
quite the showman.

35:48.162 --> 35:49.823
<i>Alakazam</i>

35:52.233 --> 35:55.600
That was a little illusion he whipped up
for my farewell tour.

35:55.770 --> 35:57.067
Wait, you two are brothers?

35:57.238 --> 36:02.005
Funny, isn't it? I get stuck with the looks,
while lucky Marlon here, the brains.

36:02.176 --> 36:05.077
Yeah, lucky me.

36:08.416 --> 36:11.977
I'm in the early stages.
Right now I can only create small things.

36:12.153 --> 36:13.984
But someday...

36:14.155 --> 36:15.645
Hey, I just had a thought.

36:15.823 --> 36:19.054
Maybe the griffin
is just like a humongous hologram.

36:19.227 --> 36:21.491
Yeah, humongous hologram.

36:21.662 --> 36:25.428
Nice try, you guys,
except holograms don't rip through trees.

36:25.600 --> 36:28.160
- Like, not even little ones?
- Sorry.

36:28.669 --> 36:32.298
By the way, Miss Crystal,
if that is your real name...

36:32.473 --> 36:35.965
...how is it that you knew exactly which
button to push to shut off the system?

36:36.143 --> 36:38.805
Uh, because it says off?

36:39.347 --> 36:41.577
- Oh.
- Lf you ask me, Whirlen...

36:41.749 --> 36:45.708
...all this electronic fakery
is exactly what's doomed your school.

36:45.887 --> 36:51.052
The students don't need to learn a lot
of hokey Las Vegas illusions.

36:51.225 --> 36:54.353
They should learn the real magic
of O'Flannery Castle...

36:54.528 --> 36:58.555
...with all of its wonder and romance.

36:58.733 --> 37:01.964
And do you have any stories of romance
you'd like to share?

37:02.136 --> 37:07.233
Heh, heh. Heavens. I'm just a caretaker.

37:07.408 --> 37:09.774
I leave the storytelling to the teachers.

37:09.944 --> 37:12.310
And if the teachers are smart...

37:12.480 --> 37:16.610
...they'll treat the tradition
of O'Flannery Castle with more respect.

37:16.784 --> 37:18.809
That's the reason
the griffin's come back.

37:18.986 --> 37:20.044
What do you mean?

37:20.221 --> 37:24.317
It's here to return the castle
to the days of true magic.

37:24.492 --> 37:26.050
The way it should be.

37:28.829 --> 37:32.492
Okay, okay, Miss Rumblebuns.
We get it. Thank you.

37:32.667 --> 37:35.727
Well, no one can say
she's not passionate about her work.

37:35.903 --> 37:36.927
[LAUGHS]

37:37.104 --> 37:39.299
Shaggy, Shaggy, Shaggy.
Oh, my gosh, I found it.

37:39.473 --> 37:40.565
I found the magic staff.

37:40.741 --> 37:44.370
You found the magic what? Yipe!

37:52.453 --> 37:54.114
MADELYN:
I was reading about Lord O'Flannery.

37:54.288 --> 37:58.622
He used a special magic staff
to summon the griffin and control it.

37:58.793 --> 38:01.057
Where is this magic staff?

38:01.228 --> 38:03.753
Lord O'Flannery had it placed
in his tomb...

38:03.931 --> 38:07.526
...which is on an island
right here in Shadow Lake.

38:07.702 --> 38:08.896
It's real close.

38:09.070 --> 38:11.334
That's the same direction
the griffin came from.

38:11.505 --> 38:15.066
AMOS: You won't wanna be going there,
my friends.

38:15.543 --> 38:17.408
What that fancy book won't tell you...

38:17.578 --> 38:20.138
...is when Lord O'Flannery
came from Ireland...

38:20.314 --> 38:23.442
...with him came his clan's banshee.

38:24.218 --> 38:27.449
Banshee, like, that's a good thing, right?

38:28.456 --> 38:32.893
It's a hideous female ghost
whose wailing dooms whoever hears it.

38:34.061 --> 38:35.528
Not listening.

38:35.696 --> 38:37.254
[HUMMING]

38:37.431 --> 38:41.959
AMOS: Legend says the banshee
wailed over Lord O'Flannery...

38:42.136 --> 38:45.333
...as he breathed his last breath.

38:45.506 --> 38:48.907
To this day, the ghost guards his tomb...

38:49.076 --> 38:55.015
...ready to attack any who would disturb
the dark wizard's slumber.

38:56.450 --> 38:59.681
You all have a pleasant evening.

39:03.357 --> 39:06.588
Alrighty, who's up for pie?

39:06.761 --> 39:10.060
Come on, Shaggy, we gotta find that staff.
It could be a clue.

39:10.231 --> 39:11.289
[SIGHS]

39:11.465 --> 39:13.729
[GIGGLING]

39:17.371 --> 39:20.966
MAN [ON GPS]: <i>Shadow Lake</i>
<i>is a quarter-mile ahead. Spooky.</i>

39:21.208 --> 39:23.199
[MAN LAUGHING ON GPS]

39:28.449 --> 39:29.939
FRED:
We better stick together, gang.

39:30.117 --> 39:32.415
Remember,
that banshee could be anywhere.

39:32.586 --> 39:36.454
Man, no matter how hard I try,
I can't forget something like that.

40:00.281 --> 40:03.614
All ashore who's going ashore.

40:24.672 --> 40:26.970
We should be getting close, gang.

40:27.141 --> 40:28.802
Through here.

40:37.651 --> 40:40.347
How about we go over?

40:45.493 --> 40:47.393
How did you do...? Oh!

40:47.561 --> 40:49.552
[FRED GRUNTING]

40:54.001 --> 40:55.969
Fred, you okay?

40:56.770 --> 40:58.067
Yeah.

40:58.239 --> 41:00.969
I guess we all have
our danger-prone days.

41:01.142 --> 41:02.473
[GIGGLES]

41:21.595 --> 41:24.325
VELMA:
I think Scooby found something.

41:31.772 --> 41:33.603
Check out this strange marking.

41:38.679 --> 41:40.613
Each monolith has its own.

41:40.781 --> 41:43.272
FRED:
And I found another on the floor.

41:48.956 --> 41:50.355
There's one here too.

41:54.962 --> 41:56.293
[GRUNTS]

41:59.633 --> 42:00.964
[RUMBLING]

42:01.835 --> 42:02.995
BOTH:
Uh-oh.

42:07.308 --> 42:09.799
Oh, well, I guess we'll never get in
that kooky crypt.

42:09.977 --> 42:13.378
Let's head back to the castle
and make enchiladas.

42:14.848 --> 42:17.316
It moved. Oh, man.

42:17.484 --> 42:19.213
Shaggy did it.

42:19.386 --> 42:21.820
Come on, I bet if we push it...

42:22.456 --> 42:25.619
FRED:
All right, everyone push.

42:39.039 --> 42:41.906
A secret door. Let's go.

42:49.083 --> 42:50.516
Scooby, run.

42:55.356 --> 42:57.381
SHAGGY:
Hurry, Scoob.

43:03.197 --> 43:04.528
Phew.

43:14.908 --> 43:16.773
VELMA:
It's the O'Flannery crest.

43:17.211 --> 43:19.406
Help me get the lid off.

43:27.588 --> 43:29.613
DAPHNE:
That must be O'Flannery's staff.

43:29.790 --> 43:32.418
And that must be O'Flannery.

43:33.127 --> 43:34.992
- I'll get it.
- Wait, wait, wait.

43:35.162 --> 43:38.188
Only the bravest hero should retrieve it.

43:38.365 --> 43:40.890
Oh, all right.

43:48.876 --> 43:50.036
[WHIMPERS]

43:56.083 --> 43:59.644
- Scooby, do you mind?
- Sorry, Shaggy.

43:59.820 --> 44:01.549
It's okay. Thanks for the hand.

44:01.722 --> 44:05.590
- Uh, uh, Shaggy.
- Zoinks.

44:07.995 --> 44:12.227
Yup, that's me, Shaggy Rogers,
the bravest of heroes.

44:12.399 --> 44:14.299
[WHOOSH]

44:14.468 --> 44:17.130
Shaggy, we have a visitor.

44:17.571 --> 44:21.905
Then, like, why is nobody saying hello?

44:22.309 --> 44:23.799
[BOTH YELP]

44:25.946 --> 44:28.915
Uh-huh. Bravest of heroes.

44:31.185 --> 44:34.552
So that's the banshee?
She doesn't look scary.

44:34.722 --> 44:36.781
Yeah, she looks kind of pretty.

44:39.760 --> 44:41.159
[SCREAMS]

44:41.328 --> 44:42.955
[ALL SCREAM]

44:48.435 --> 44:50.096
FRED:
Out here.

44:54.274 --> 44:56.265
[SCREAMING]

44:59.279 --> 45:01.110
We gotta get back to the boat.

45:01.281 --> 45:04.478
We can't leave the staff. Come on.

45:11.158 --> 45:12.955
DAPHNE: Where'd they go?
FRED: They'll be here.

45:13.127 --> 45:14.424
Let's get the boat turned around.

45:14.595 --> 45:15.960
[BANSHEE SCREAMING]

45:17.865 --> 45:18.957
Madelyn!

45:21.668 --> 45:23.659
MADELYN:
Coming through.

45:36.383 --> 45:38.544
DAPHNE:
Push us off, Shaggy.

45:58.005 --> 45:59.131
[VELMA GASPS]

46:04.745 --> 46:06.736
[ALL GROANING]

46:21.161 --> 46:22.958
Nice footwork, Shaggy.

46:23.130 --> 46:26.327
Let's get this back to the castle
and analyze it for clues.

46:26.500 --> 46:29.196
I can't believe
how you saved us like that.

46:29.903 --> 46:33.964
Yeah, well, I do have some major feet.

46:34.141 --> 46:36.405
It's more than your feet, Shaggy.

46:36.577 --> 46:40.707
It's you. You're so amazing, so forceful.

46:40.881 --> 46:44.942
I think you're the bravest,
most wonderful boy I have ever known.

46:45.586 --> 46:51.183
Oh, gee, Madelyn. I like you too.

46:51.358 --> 46:54.350
Aw. Mwah, mwah, mwah.

46:54.528 --> 46:56.325
It's getting late.

46:57.130 --> 46:59.155
[CREATURE SCREECHES]

47:02.936 --> 47:04.426
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY YELP]

47:07.908 --> 47:11.674
MAN [ON GPS]: <i>What are you waiting for?</i>
<i>Directions? Drive!</i>

47:32.466 --> 47:33.592
SHAGGY:
Shoo, griffin.

47:33.767 --> 47:36.258
Like, be gone already.

47:38.438 --> 47:40.565
I think the batteries are dead.

47:40.741 --> 47:45.337
Hey, I put a box of magic explosives
in the van for practice on the field.

47:45.512 --> 47:48.675
Like, Scooby-Doo,
let's strike this griffin out.

47:48.849 --> 47:50.840
Yeah, strike-out.

48:01.094 --> 48:02.686
[TRUCK HORN HONKING]

48:09.937 --> 48:13.373
Uh-oh. I think Scooby dropped
a live explosive in the box.

48:13.540 --> 48:16.338
- Like, which one?
- I can't tell.

48:29.990 --> 48:31.890
We haven't lost him yet, guys.

48:36.964 --> 48:38.454
[TIRES SCREECHING]

48:43.170 --> 48:45.730
Hurry, inside.

48:46.106 --> 48:48.506
MAN [ON GPS]:
<i>Hey, you're gonna leave me out here?</i>

48:52.379 --> 48:54.244
What's all the ruckus?

48:54.414 --> 48:55.813
[GRIFFIN SCREECHES]

48:56.883 --> 48:59.875
Griffin attack, run.

49:00.554 --> 49:01.816
Huh?

49:09.029 --> 49:11.020
Let's get the staff to Whirlen.

49:11.465 --> 49:12.796
[GASPS]

49:16.937 --> 49:18.063
Oh, no.

49:18.238 --> 49:19.569
Like, don't do it.

49:26.647 --> 49:27.671
[MADELYN SCREAMS]

49:27.848 --> 49:32.547
- Madelyn!
MADELYN: Velma!

49:32.719 --> 49:34.710
SHAGGY:
Oh, no.

49:36.390 --> 49:40.656
Mr. Curdles, events have taken
a terrible turn over here.

49:40.827 --> 49:43.455
You might wanna see for yourself.

49:55.676 --> 49:57.268
WHIRLEN:
I don't understand.

49:57.444 --> 49:59.742
Why are you taking
all these magic tricks?

49:59.913 --> 50:02.381
They're the only weapons we have
against the griffin.

50:02.549 --> 50:05.313
But you don't even know
where the griffin's taken her.

50:05.485 --> 50:07.112
We have a pretty good idea.

50:07.287 --> 50:10.188
We believe it's called the Griffin's Roost
for a reason.

50:10.357 --> 50:12.757
The Griffin's Roost? But it's not safe.

50:12.926 --> 50:15.622
The whole place is liable to crash down
on your heads.

50:15.796 --> 50:18.321
We'll be careful.
Besides, if there are any clues...

50:18.498 --> 50:19.829
...I'm sure we'll find them there.

50:20.000 --> 50:21.331
[METAL CLANGING]

50:26.473 --> 50:28.668
Like, I'm ready.

50:30.644 --> 50:32.202
Why are you wearing armor?

50:32.379 --> 50:36.873
Because even with this magic doohickey,
I need all the protection I can get.

50:38.452 --> 50:40.443
Whirly, are you all right?

50:40.620 --> 50:43.316
This griffin business has beaten me,
Marlon.

50:43.490 --> 50:47.051
It's time to bring down the curtain
on this magic school.

50:47.227 --> 50:48.888
My dream.

50:49.062 --> 50:51.053
[CLAPPING]

50:53.366 --> 50:55.994
Touching. Touching.

50:56.169 --> 50:58.694
Your most heartfelt performance,
Whirlen.

50:58.872 --> 51:00.863
Now, rejoice.

51:01.041 --> 51:02.668
Kindly Calvin Curdles is here...

51:02.843 --> 51:06.142
...with the silver lining
to your cloud of despair.

51:06.313 --> 51:07.541
How did you get in?

51:07.714 --> 51:09.306
Through the door.

51:09.483 --> 51:14.147
I'm prepared to take
this monster-blighted castle off your hands.

51:14.321 --> 51:18.121
I'll even give you a third... No, no, no.

51:18.291 --> 51:22.057
Make that an eighth
of what you paid for it.

51:25.098 --> 51:28.556
Well, this is hardly the time
for real-estate transactions.

51:28.735 --> 51:30.430
When it comes to business matters...

51:30.604 --> 51:34.233
...Calvin Curdles was never one
to consider people's feelings.

51:34.407 --> 51:38.036
Now, now, Alma,
perhaps I'm doing us all a favor.

51:38.211 --> 51:41.544
You've said there was no griffin
before these two took over the castle.

51:41.715 --> 51:45.674
- But we're not to blame.
- It's okay, Marlon.

51:46.386 --> 51:47.717
Where do I sign?

51:50.457 --> 51:52.618
I think you should wait till we get back.

51:52.793 --> 51:56.559
There's more to this griffin business
than meets the eye.

51:56.730 --> 52:00.598
You know, I really, really don't like her.

52:00.767 --> 52:04.203
Just give us an hour. Let's go, guys.

52:05.372 --> 52:06.703
[SNARLS]

52:53.486 --> 52:54.510
[CLEARS THROAT]

52:58.825 --> 53:00.816
[SCREAMS]

53:19.779 --> 53:22.407
- What happened?
- Like, it was the banshee.

53:22.582 --> 53:24.675
But she split when Scooby tripped.

53:25.852 --> 53:26.944
VELMA:
It's a wire.

53:36.363 --> 53:39.958
- What is it, a camera?
- I don't think so, Fred.

53:40.133 --> 53:42.101
MADELYN:
Help! Help!

53:42.269 --> 53:43.793
Madelyn.

53:43.970 --> 53:45.631
Madelyn? Where?

53:46.206 --> 53:48.197
Up here.

53:50.644 --> 53:52.134
[MADELYN SCREAMS]

53:53.179 --> 53:55.670
MADELYN:
Help! Help!

53:57.984 --> 53:59.781
Help!

54:04.224 --> 54:08.354
Can anybody hear me? Help!

54:11.331 --> 54:13.322
[CRYING]

54:29.015 --> 54:30.573
[SCREAMS]

54:42.095 --> 54:44.427
The stair moved.

54:55.875 --> 54:57.866
[THUDS]

55:01.614 --> 55:03.275
FRED:
Here's a way out.

55:21.601 --> 55:23.967
MADELYN:
Help! Help!

55:24.137 --> 55:25.764
She's on the other side.

55:26.573 --> 55:28.006
[CRACK]

55:28.174 --> 55:30.165
[CREAKING]

55:44.090 --> 55:46.081
[SCREECHING]

55:52.098 --> 55:53.622
Try the staff again.

55:53.800 --> 55:55.734
The staff?

56:00.974 --> 56:04.876
Like, you shall not pass, man.

56:10.150 --> 56:11.481
It worked.

56:11.651 --> 56:13.380
[LAUGHING]

56:14.721 --> 56:16.018
[GRIFFIN GROWLS]

56:16.189 --> 56:17.656
It didn't work.

56:18.358 --> 56:19.882
We're done for.

56:26.833 --> 56:28.164
[SCREECHES]

56:30.236 --> 56:32.067
Not yet.

56:34.507 --> 56:36.236
Let him have it.

56:47.654 --> 56:49.485
The smoke bombs.

57:06.573 --> 57:08.564
[GIGGLING]

57:09.342 --> 57:11.207
FRED:
Run!

57:24.858 --> 57:28.259
Shaggy, Scooby, are you okay?

57:31.264 --> 57:33.755
Like, I think I still have all my pieces.

57:33.933 --> 57:36.595
FRED:
Stay there, we'll come back with help.

57:36.769 --> 57:39.795
That's the best idea I've heard,
like, ever.

57:41.641 --> 57:43.632
[GRIFFIN SCREECHES]

57:47.780 --> 57:50.146
SCOOBY: The griffin.
- It's back.

57:50.316 --> 57:52.716
But, like, Fred told us to stay right here.

57:56.856 --> 58:00.952
Help! Help! Can anybody hear me?

58:01.127 --> 58:04.756
Like, she'll probably be okay
until help comes, don't you think?

58:04.931 --> 58:07.661
Shaggy, Madelyn likes you.

58:07.834 --> 58:11.065
Well, since you put it that way, Scoob.

58:22.649 --> 58:26.779
Like, dude, peep that crazy lock,
and that's without the key.

58:28.188 --> 58:29.678
Shaggy, look.

58:29.956 --> 58:30.980
Huh?

58:33.226 --> 58:35.194
Good work, Scoob.

58:38.198 --> 58:39.927
Yeah.

59:13.933 --> 59:15.833
Shaggy.

59:16.002 --> 59:17.492
Hey, Mads, you okay?

59:17.670 --> 59:19.604
I am now.

59:21.541 --> 59:24.738
I mean, the griffin dropped me in the tower,
then flew off.

59:24.911 --> 59:27.505
I hope he doesn't come back
for a midnight snack.

59:27.747 --> 59:29.078
[GRIFFIN GROWLING]

59:39.659 --> 59:43.117
SHAGGY: Quick, Scooby-Doo, pull something
out of that bag that will help us escape.

59:43.296 --> 59:45.059
Okay.

01:00:04.884 --> 01:00:06.283
We can climb down on these.

01:00:07.954 --> 01:00:11.321
Like, I don't know.
It seems kind of flimsy.

01:00:12.091 --> 01:00:13.922
[SCOOBY & SHAGGY SCREAM]

01:00:14.627 --> 01:00:17.187
- Come on.
SCOOBY: Go.

01:00:46.292 --> 01:00:48.157
Like, beat it, Tweety.

01:00:57.904 --> 01:01:00.372
Where's the seat belt on this thing?

01:01:00.540 --> 01:01:01.973
[MADELYN SCREAMS]

01:01:02.408 --> 01:01:04.069
CURDLES:
Those kids won't find anything.

01:01:04.243 --> 01:01:05.767
Why delay the inevitable?

01:01:07.146 --> 01:01:09.512
I suppose you're right.

01:01:09.682 --> 01:01:12.150
But I do hate letting down my students.

01:01:12.318 --> 01:01:14.809
Oh, yes, it's a tragedy. Sign here, please.

01:01:26.999 --> 01:01:28.660
The griffin is in the old tower.

01:01:30.436 --> 01:01:32.370
Come on.

01:01:41.447 --> 01:01:42.505
There they are.

01:01:47.987 --> 01:01:50.114
MADELYN:
Shaggy, try the staff again.

01:01:50.289 --> 01:01:53.190
- Dude, it's a fake.
- Just try.

01:01:54.961 --> 01:01:56.724
I totally command you.

01:01:56.896 --> 01:02:01.299
By the powers of Houdini,
the Wizard of Oz...

01:02:01.467 --> 01:02:04.766
...and, um, the English kid
with the glasses...

01:02:04.937 --> 01:02:07.371
...to put us down.

01:02:15.381 --> 01:02:18.373
Like, dude, we're losing altitude.

01:02:29.829 --> 01:02:31.990
Little help, little help!

01:02:44.076 --> 01:02:46.943
Shaggy got him. Isn't that incredible?

01:02:48.748 --> 01:02:50.079
Yeah.

01:02:50.716 --> 01:02:52.581
You really are brave.

01:02:52.752 --> 01:02:55.778
Like, don't squeeze me, Madelyn.

01:02:55.955 --> 01:02:58.355
You're denting my metal.

01:02:58.558 --> 01:03:00.116
[GRIFFIN ROARS]

01:03:10.436 --> 01:03:13.735
The poor thing looks hurt.
Why doesn't it fly away?

01:03:13.906 --> 01:03:15.897
[METAL CREAKING]

01:03:16.742 --> 01:03:18.937
There's your answer.

01:03:33.759 --> 01:03:37.855
- The griffin, it's a gigantic puppet?
VELMA: Correct.

01:03:38.030 --> 01:03:40.464
This whole charade is making sense now.

01:03:44.303 --> 01:03:45.930
Run!

01:03:46.105 --> 01:03:47.697
MARLON:
Whoa.

01:03:56.249 --> 01:03:58.581
Marlon, you?

01:03:58.751 --> 01:04:03.415
Marlon operated that contraption trying
to scare everyone away once and for all.

01:04:03.589 --> 01:04:05.750
But Shaggy and Scooby spoiled his plans.

01:04:07.994 --> 01:04:10.155
So the monster never was real.

01:04:10.329 --> 01:04:14.493
No, just a more sophisticated version
of the puppets in your magic act...

01:04:14.667 --> 01:04:16.259
...when you and Marlon were kids.

01:04:16.435 --> 01:04:20.132
The blimp carried the griffin beneath it
to make it look like it was flying.

01:04:20.306 --> 01:04:22.297
But how did he disguise the blimp?

01:04:22.475 --> 01:04:25.774
Remember how every time
the griffin appeared, it was foggy?

01:04:25.945 --> 01:04:30.143
The blimp generated
its own concealing fog bank.

01:04:32.852 --> 01:04:36.549
I noticed some of the bottles
in Marlon's workshop were marked glycerol.

01:04:36.722 --> 01:04:40.988
A chemical used by professional illusionists
in fog machines.

01:04:41.160 --> 01:04:43.128
I used the fog to hide the blimp...

01:04:43.296 --> 01:04:47.130
...then worked the griffin through
this handheld animatronic control.

01:04:48.034 --> 01:04:50.093
[ROARS]

01:04:51.504 --> 01:04:53.938
What about when the griffin attacked us
in the tower?

01:04:54.106 --> 01:04:57.507
- It couldn't have been the same puppet.
- It wasn't.

01:04:57.910 --> 01:05:02.313
After Whirlen bought the castle,
I started renovating the Griffin's Roost.

01:05:02.782 --> 01:05:07.082
I discovered Lord O' Flannery had rigged
parts of the tower with devices of his own...

01:05:07.253 --> 01:05:10.086
...to make superstitious people
think a monster lived there.

01:05:10.256 --> 01:05:12.087
When trespassers entered the tower...

01:05:12.258 --> 01:05:15.125
...they would be driven away
by the attacking griffin.

01:05:15.294 --> 01:05:16.693
I kept the secret to myself...

01:05:16.862 --> 01:05:20.195
...and outfitted the worn-out machinery
with state-of-the-art equipment.

01:05:23.469 --> 01:05:25.733
Okay, but who is the banshee?

01:05:25.905 --> 01:05:27.805
- Another puppet, right?
- Partially.

01:05:27.974 --> 01:05:31.205
Marlon had several rigged
to appear in various places.

01:05:31.377 --> 01:05:34.039
Even in the lake,
to make it look like she was chasing us.

01:05:34.213 --> 01:05:36.113
She wasn't a puppet every time.

01:05:36.282 --> 01:05:40.048
Yes, I realized that when we saw the device
in the tower.

01:05:40.219 --> 01:05:44.178
It was really a projector Marlon uses
for his volumetric displays.

01:05:44.357 --> 01:05:46.018
One of many.

01:05:46.192 --> 01:05:50.629
Anyone entering the tower would
have set off an invisible electric eye...

01:05:51.998 --> 01:05:54.364
...activating the ghost.

01:05:56.135 --> 01:06:00.196
Marlon's technology was a lot more
sophisticated than he was letting on.

01:06:00.373 --> 01:06:03.103
Marlon, why did you do this?

01:06:03.275 --> 01:06:06.540
Because all my life I've been jealous,
jealous of you.

01:06:06.712 --> 01:06:09.442
While I did all the work,
you got all the applause.

01:06:09.615 --> 01:06:12.448
I finally decided
I wanted to create my own magic act.

01:06:12.618 --> 01:06:16.315
With my puppets and projections,
I could become a magic sensation.

01:06:16.489 --> 01:06:17.649
Why didn't you?

01:06:17.823 --> 01:06:19.757
Because I needed money to start the act.

01:06:19.925 --> 01:06:23.088
The only way I could get it
is if you agreed to sell the castle...

01:06:23.262 --> 01:06:26.163
...which I knew you wouldn't do
unless you were forced to.

01:06:26.332 --> 01:06:29.096
I didn't mean to hurt anyone, honest.

01:06:29.268 --> 01:06:31.759
All I wanted to do
was scare people away.

01:06:31.937 --> 01:06:33.370
I tried to make amends.

01:06:33.539 --> 01:06:37.066
After the automated griffin wrecked
the bridge, I flew back in the blimp...

01:06:37.243 --> 01:06:38.369
...to bring you down.

01:06:38.544 --> 01:06:43.106
But these two fearless souls attacked me
before I could explain.

01:06:43.849 --> 01:06:47.717
- Hey, how did the griffin crash anyway?
- Here's your answer.

01:06:47.887 --> 01:06:49.286
The magic staff?

01:06:49.455 --> 01:06:53.016
Like, I guess,
it really did control the monster after all.

01:06:53.859 --> 01:06:55.986
Aw, I'm so ashamed.

01:06:56.162 --> 01:06:58.153
[CRYING]

01:07:03.602 --> 01:07:07.629
Who would have thought
that miserable Marlon would be behind this?

01:07:07.807 --> 01:07:10.298
You would. You knew all along.

01:07:12.144 --> 01:07:16.979
Of course, Amos was the only one
who was never afraid to be out at night.

01:07:17.149 --> 01:07:19.583
He must have known the griffin
was a fake.

01:07:19.752 --> 01:07:22.277
Amos probably followed Marlon
to the Griffin's Roost...

01:07:22.455 --> 01:07:24.480
...while he was rebuilding it.

01:07:24.690 --> 01:07:29.559
AMOS: I saw him going in there, day and
night, with loads of strange-Iooking crates.

01:07:29.729 --> 01:07:31.856
So I got nosy and peeked.

01:07:32.031 --> 01:07:35.865
Yes, and my guess is he told you,
Mr. Curdles.

01:07:36.035 --> 01:07:38.026
You weren't worried about the griffin.

01:07:38.204 --> 01:07:41.105
You could even use it
to get a cheap price on the castle.

01:07:41.273 --> 01:07:45.437
- Wow. These girlies are smart.
- Oh, shut up.

01:07:45.978 --> 01:07:48.139
No need to deny it, Mr. Curdles.

01:07:48.314 --> 01:07:51.112
Your story about turning the castle
into a restaurant...

01:07:51.283 --> 01:07:53.410
...never made sense in the first place.

01:07:53.586 --> 01:07:57.078
You were really buying it
for Miss Rumblebuns, weren't you?

01:07:57.256 --> 01:07:59.087
Calvin, is this true?

01:07:59.625 --> 01:08:03.186
Yes, Alma, it is.
I meant for it to be a surprise.

01:08:03.729 --> 01:08:07.062
You see, years ago, I operated a struggling
ice-cream concession here...

01:08:07.233 --> 01:08:11.294
...for the few tourists
who visited O' Flannery Castle.

01:08:16.008 --> 01:08:21.412
It was here that I met the castle's dazzling
caretaker, Miss Alma Rumblebuns.

01:08:25.451 --> 01:08:29.581
Ah. We were so much in love.

01:08:29.822 --> 01:08:32.154
Fearing that a high-born creature
of Alma's caste...

01:08:32.323 --> 01:08:37.193
...could never settle
for a mere sherbet jockey, I left.

01:08:37.363 --> 01:08:40.957
Determined someday
to return a frozen-novelty mogul.

01:08:41.133 --> 01:08:45.934
Alas, I became so swept up in
the intoxicating world of cream and cones...

01:08:46.104 --> 01:08:48.868
...I never came back.

01:08:49.475 --> 01:08:51.636
But I couldn't forget you, Alma.

01:08:51.810 --> 01:08:55.577
I thought that if I bought you this castle
which you loved so much...

01:08:55.747 --> 01:08:58.080
...you might love me again.

01:08:58.716 --> 01:09:00.912
Oh, Calvin, I don't know what to say.

01:09:02.421 --> 01:09:06.050
Well, just say you forgive me.

01:09:07.993 --> 01:09:09.323
Ew.

01:09:12.598 --> 01:09:15.828
Please, Whirlen, I will double the price.

01:09:16.001 --> 01:09:19.095
Don't do it, Whirlen,
I couldn't take the money now.

01:09:19.270 --> 01:09:21.761
Not when I've seen
what the school means to you.

01:09:21.941 --> 01:09:23.305
I was wrong.

01:09:23.475 --> 01:09:25.067
My place is here with you...

01:09:25.243 --> 01:09:28.407
...passing on what we've discovered to kids
who truly wanna learn.

01:09:28.581 --> 01:09:30.845
They're the ones I've really hurt.

01:09:31.317 --> 01:09:33.979
I think there's time to make amends.

01:09:36.988 --> 01:09:40.857
Starting with the education
of our new apprentice, Madelyn Dinkley.

01:09:41.026 --> 01:09:42.857
Really? You mean it?

01:09:43.028 --> 01:09:48.761
With your enthusiasm and our coaching,
you could be the next big thing in magic.

01:09:48.934 --> 01:09:52.370
Congratulations, Madelyn. You deserve it.

01:09:52.537 --> 01:09:56.702
I must admit, you handled yourself
pretty well on this adventure.

01:09:56.876 --> 01:10:02.041
Thanks, I guess we Dinkley sisters
have something in common after all.

01:10:07.152 --> 01:10:08.278
CURDLES:
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

01:10:08.854 --> 01:10:13.382
The Cone Castle Creamery, makers
of those cones that make you moan...

01:10:13.559 --> 01:10:16.050
...is proud to sponsor
the very first show...

01:10:16.228 --> 01:10:20.187
...by the students of the Merlin Brothers'
Academy of Magic.

01:10:20.366 --> 01:10:23.699
And now your hosts,
Marlon and Whirlen...

01:10:23.869 --> 01:10:27.965
...the Brothers Merlin.

01:10:28.140 --> 01:10:30.404
[AUDIENCE CLAPPING]

01:10:33.078 --> 01:10:35.069
[AUDIENCE OOHING]

01:10:43.656 --> 01:10:46.648
- Isn't she adorable?
- Yeah.

01:10:46.825 --> 01:10:51.091
- Hey, shouldn't you be up there with her?
- I've been training an assistant.

01:10:52.531 --> 01:10:54.522
[AUDIENCE CLAPPING]

01:11:14.586 --> 01:11:16.383
[ROARS]

01:11:20.125 --> 01:11:24.755
- How did you do that?
- That's my secret, scarf boy.

01:11:24.964 --> 01:11:29.230
- Like, that was totally awesome, Mads.
- Thanks, Shaggy.

01:11:29.401 --> 01:11:32.393
Hey, have you seen Scooby-Doo?

01:11:36.041 --> 01:11:39.568
- Oh.
- Let's go, move, move, move.

01:11:39.745 --> 01:11:43.545
[ROARING]

01:11:45.651 --> 01:11:47.744
[BARKING]

01:11:47.920 --> 01:11:49.387
[LION MEWS]

01:11:49.822 --> 01:11:51.813
[AUDIENCE CHEERING AND CLAPPING]

01:11:53.325 --> 01:11:56.158
Looks like your dog is braver
than you thought.

01:11:56.328 --> 01:12:01.425
Thank you, thank you, thank you.
And thank you.

01:12:04.636 --> 01:12:09.073
Scooby-abracadabra-Doo!

